A containres  is like  a  lightweight  box that has everything  your application  need to run

*the app code
*ssytem libraries(Python,Django,Nginx, etc)
*dependencies(like database drivers)

but unlike a virtual machine , a container does not  carry  full OS it shares the host machines OS  KERNEL

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*Docker is the most popular container tool.
*Docker uses  the linux kernel  feature (namespace and cgroup) to isolate the apps
*YOu package your a;; in a docker image -> then run it as a container

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Container lifecycle
------------------

1.Build -> Create a Docker iamge 
2.Run    -> Start a container form that image
3.Stop  -> Pause or shut down the container
4.Remove -> Delete it when not needed

docker build -t myapp .
docker run -d  -p 8000:8000 myapp
docker ps 
docker stop container_id
docker rm containre_id

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CONTAINERS ON A SERVER OR EC2
----------------------------

*On your local laptop -> you install the docker then run containers
*ON an ec2 instnace -> you install Docker in the vm ,then run the same containers
*since contianers are protable the same image works on your laptop ,ec2 or kubernetes cluster

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
why containers are better than just running Django normally

*your app runs the same every where
*you can send the image instead of givving setup insturction
*scalable -> Kubernetes can run 100's of containers form the same image
